1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,127
- [tense music]
- [Jalil] <i>Where is Father?</i>

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:04,295
[Jamilah] <i>They abducted him</i>
<i>and then imprisoned him.</i>

3
00:00:04,379 --> 00:00:05,922
<i>He was their leader.</i>

4
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:09,259
[breathes deeply] <i>The person</i>
<i>who destroyed our community.</i>

5
00:00:10,343 --> 00:00:12,053
[Lara] <i>What happened to Oliver</i>
<i>and the others wasn't your fault.</i>

6
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:14,264
If you really believe
you're being silenced,

7
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:17,308
then find out what's the truth
before it's too late.

8
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,852
Solve this, Marcus.

9
00:00:18,935 --> 00:00:20,562
For our colleagues.

10
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:22,397
How come it's now empty?

11
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,524
[Marcus] <i>Sir, I'm sorry.</i>
<i>Everything got deleted.</i>

12
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:26,359
Do you know who did it?

13
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:28,820
I don't know anything
about what you're saying.

14
00:00:28,903 --> 00:00:29,738
All I know is that

15
00:00:29,821 --> 00:00:32,991
the person standing right in front of me
was the one in charge

16
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:35,160
when they started killing my neighbors!

17
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:36,911
I didn't like what happened back there!

18
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:38,663
Your case will be resolved more easily

19
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:41,499
If you cooperate with me. Remember that.

20
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:44,627
[Azuelo] Why did you interrogate
a high-value suspect

21
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:45,795
without permission?

22
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,505
[Marcus] <i>Aside from my colleagues,</i>
<i>he witnessed</i>

23
00:00:47,589 --> 00:00:49,966
<i>how everything went wrong</i>
<i>during the Zamboanga operation!</i>

24
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:52,177
There you go again, Agent Reyes!

25
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:55,138
For now, take a break, Agent Reyes.

26
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:57,474
[Azuelo] <i>Turn in your gun and badge.</i>

27
00:00:57,557 --> 00:01:00,852
<i>I'll give them back to you</i>
<i>as soon as your suspension is over.</i>

28
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,270
And this is for your own good.

29
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:05,982
[Jalil] <i>I'm going to correct all of this.</i>

30
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:09,360
<i>They only implicated us</i>
<i>because we can easily be blamed.</i>

31
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:11,071
<i>But I won't stop</i>

32
00:01:11,654 --> 00:01:15,950
<i>until I get revenge for our people.</i>

33
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:18,411
[music concludes]

34
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:27,086
[mysterious theme music playing]

35
00:01:39,015 --> 00:01:45,230
[engine whirring]

36
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,863
[dramatic music playing]

37
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:19,222
[dramatic music continues]

38
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,249
- [Mataverde] Alright, listen up.
- [music concludes]

39
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:50,420
Tomorrow, we'll transfer
to a more secure facility

40
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:52,338
our high-profile detainee,

41
00:02:52,422 --> 00:02:54,674
- Datu Rahman Abubakar.
- [tense music]

42
00:02:54,757 --> 00:02:57,176
[Azuelo] Someone might try to block us.

43
00:02:57,260 --> 00:03:01,306
That's why everyone
must strictly follow protocol.

44
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:05,059
Agent Lara Angeles will lead
this transfer.

45
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:06,686
Copy that, sir.

46
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,771
SPO1 Sabdani!

47
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,148
Sir.

48
00:03:10,231 --> 00:03:12,817
You are in charge
of the detainee's security detail.

49
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:14,277
Understood, sir.

50
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:17,030
[Tabuzo] Make sure
that Datu Rahman arrives

51
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,656
at the new facility alive.

52
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:20,700
Is that clear?

53
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:22,577
Understood, sir.

54
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,078
Alright, everyone.

55
00:03:24,662 --> 00:03:25,955
Check your equipment.

56
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:26,915
Get some rest.

57
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:28,499
Everyone comes back.

58
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,293
- Yes, sir!
- Dismissed.

59
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:32,921
[tense music playing]

60
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:37,383
[indistinct chattering]

61
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:41,346
[indistinct chattering]

62
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:48,102
[music fades]

63
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:55,526
[motorcycle engine revving]

64
00:03:56,152 --> 00:04:01,741
[somber music playing]

65
00:04:12,335 --> 00:04:13,753
[dog whimpers]

66
00:04:17,882 --> 00:04:21,261
[somber music continues]

67
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:23,221
[cock crows]

68
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,399
- [distant shouting]
- [cock crows]

69
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:38,194
[papers rustling]

70
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:48,955
[indistinct chattering]

71
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:03,303
[Omar] Wait!

72
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:08,808
[music concludes]

73
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:12,854
[melancholic music]

74
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:22,697
[music concludes]

75
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:31,039
[suspenseful music playing]

76
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,918
What are you doing here?
Aren't you suspended?

77
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,837
[music concludes]

78
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,797
I know what's going on, Lara.

79
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,091
[somber music]

80
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:43,009
[Lara] What?

81
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:47,472
The man who attacked Oliver…

82
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:50,183
He's not just a hitman of a syndicate.

83
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:54,687
He was highly trained
and skilled. I fought him.

84
00:05:55,855 --> 00:05:57,899
This means that group is different.

85
00:05:57,982 --> 00:05:59,609
And they won't stop

86
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:01,903
until they erase all the evidence.

87
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,362
So what are you saying, Marcus?

88
00:06:03,946 --> 00:06:05,990
I know who their next target is.

89
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:07,784
Who?

90
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:09,952
Datu Rahman.

91
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:12,955
Wait.

92
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:14,916
Are you sure of what you're saying?

93
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,542
Lara, think about it.

94
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:19,253
Why did they sabotage our mission?

95
00:06:20,379 --> 00:06:22,590
Why did they force a mess on the island?

96
00:06:22,673 --> 00:06:25,635
They used our group because they wanted us

97
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:29,138
to take Datu Rahman to Manila.

98
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:31,182
And upon arriving here,

99
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:35,394
they will find a way
to get Datu Rahman from our custody.

100
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:36,395
There's…

101
00:06:36,896 --> 00:06:39,440
There's… There's a command given earlier.

102
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:42,819
We have to move Datu Rahman
to a new facility.

103
00:06:43,528 --> 00:06:44,946
They just told us today.

104
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:47,156
If my hunch is right,

105
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,408
they're not moving Datu Rahman
to secure him.

106
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:51,202
They're going to kill Datu Rahman.

107
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:52,328
Look…

108
00:06:52,411 --> 00:06:56,165
Even if this were true,
that's highly unlikely.

109
00:06:56,249 --> 00:07:00,211
Datu Rahman is in maximum security
during and after the transport.

110
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:02,380
And he has a full security detail.

111
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:06,676
I am the assigned lead
in Datu Rahman's transport planning.

112
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:10,096
We can't underestimate them, Lara.

113
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:14,308
We still don't know who the real enemy is.

114
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:16,602
[clicks tongue]

115
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:19,439
So, what's your plan?

116
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:23,609
[sighs]

117
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:26,362
[tense music]

118
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,406
[Mia] <i>We won't stay silent!</i>

119
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:30,992
According to the Special
Investigations Division,

120
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:35,496
high-value detainee Datu Rahman
will be transferred to another facility.

121
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:38,958
<i>Activists and protesters</i>
<i>gathered earlier today</i>

122
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,835
<i>in front of SID headquarters</i>

123
00:07:40,918 --> 00:07:43,629
<i>to monitor the upcoming transport.</i>

124
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:48,551
<i>And now, they call</i>
<i>for justice for Zamboanga</i>

125
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:50,553
<i>and justice for Datu Rahman.</i>

126
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:53,639
- [Mia] <i>Justice!</i>
- [activists] <i>Justice!</i>

127
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:57,143
[Mia] <i>We want justice!</i>

128
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:00,855
[chanting] We want justice!

129
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:04,567
- Justice!
- Justice!

130
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:07,528
- Justice!
- Justice!

131
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:10,948
[crowd chanting] Justice!

132
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:14,452
[crowd chanting] Justice!

133
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:17,747
[crowd chanting] Justice!

134
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:21,584
- [activist 1] Free Datu Rahman!
- [activists] Free him!

135
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:23,920
[activist 1] Free Datu Rahman!

136
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,379
[activists] Free him!

137
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:27,423
[activist 1] Free Datu Rahman!

138
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,925
[activists] Free him!

139
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:32,178
[chanting] We want justice!

140
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:35,515
- Justice!
- Justice!

141
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:37,642
- Sabdani.
- [activists] Justice!

142
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:39,435
- Justice!
- Justice!

143
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,229
Do your job right, okay?

144
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:45,233
We don't want to catch you
letting Datu Rahman escape.

145
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:49,403
[activists] Justice!

146
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:50,780
You're a Muslim, right?

147
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,741
Remember this.

148
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:55,826
You're a cop.

149
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:59,247
You're not the criminal's friend.

150
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:01,707
[activist] Justice for Datu Rahman!

151
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,668
[activists] Justice!

152
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:07,547
[activists shouting]

153
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:08,589
[indistinct shouting]

154
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:13,886
[activists] Justice!

155
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:18,766
- [activists] Justice!
- [dramatic whoosh]

156
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:21,394
SID TFA IS DEAD!

157
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:25,064
- [intriguing music]
- [activists] Justice!

158
00:09:25,147 --> 00:09:27,525
- Justice!
- Justice!

159
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:30,695
- Justice!
- Justice!

160
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:35,283
- Justice!
- Justice!

161
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:39,537
- [woman] Justice!
- [activists] Justice!

162
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:42,331
- Justice!
- Justice!

163
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:43,958
- Justice!
- Justice!

164
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:47,670
- [intriguing music continues]
- [activists] Justice!

165
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:49,297
[activists] Justice!

166
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:53,551
[Mia] We're not going to stop
until we get justice!

167
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:54,969
[activists] Justice!

168
00:09:55,052 --> 00:09:57,680
[Mia] Free Datu Rahman!

169
00:09:57,763 --> 00:10:00,725
[activists] Justice!

170
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:06,147
[activists chanting]

171
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,149
[woman] Justice!

172
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:09,942
[overlapping chanting]

173
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:12,903
[Mia] Let Datu Rahman go!

174
00:10:13,404 --> 00:10:15,823
Free him, you bastards!

175
00:10:17,575 --> 00:10:20,411
- [activists] Justice!
- [overlapping chanting]

176
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,590
Free Datu Rahman!

177
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:34,800
[woman] Free Datu Rahman!

178
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:39,180
[man] Justice!

179
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:40,556
[overlapping chanting]

180
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,474
[radio crackles]

181
00:10:41,557 --> 00:10:44,518
All units, formation.
High-value detainee exiting.

182
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,896
- Maintain perimeter.
- [radio beeps]

183
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:48,981
[man] Free him!

184
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:50,316
- [overlapping chanting]
- Copy.

185
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:54,737
The detainee is secured in the vehicle.

186
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,114
- [radio crackles]
- We're leaving.

187
00:10:57,198 --> 00:10:59,825
Convoy en route to secure facility.

188
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:01,410
All units, move.

189
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:03,037
Maintain perimeter.

190
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,455
- [radio beeps]
- Roger. Copy that.

191
00:11:04,538 --> 00:11:06,123
SID TFA FAILED!

192
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:07,917
[music turns dramatic]

193
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:11,045
[activists yelling, overlapping]

194
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:17,593
[car horns honking]

195
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:29,730
[activists screaming indistinctly]

196
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:36,028
[dramatic music continues]

197
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:42,868
[car beeps]

198
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:55,214
[activists chanting] We want justice!

199
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:57,925
[activists chanting] Justice!

200
00:11:58,008 --> 00:12:00,636
[activists chanting] Justice!

201
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:03,180
[activists chanting] Justice!

202
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:06,559
[activists chanting] Justice!

203
00:12:06,642 --> 00:12:08,436
[car beeps]

204
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:14,400
[dramatic music continues]

205
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:19,029
- [siren wailing]
- [tense music playing]

206
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:22,241
[hissing sound]

207
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:31,208
[engine revving, tires screech]

208
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:33,836
[indistinct shouting in distance]

209
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:36,380
[Mia] Justice for Zamboanga!

210
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,257
Free Datu Rahman!

211
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:40,759
- Free him!
- [activists] Open up!

212
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:42,803
Command, this is Vehicle 2!
We're being mobbed!

213
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:44,680
We need crowd control assistance!

214
00:12:44,763 --> 00:12:46,724
[activists] Justice now! Justice now!

215
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:52,771
- [activists] Justice! Justice!
- [man] It's not moving!

216
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:56,275
- [man] Get out! Get out!
- Justice! Justice! Justice!

217
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:57,610
[muffled voice] We want justice!

218
00:12:57,693 --> 00:12:59,945
Justice now! Justice now!

219
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:02,406
[activists chanting] Justice!

220
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:03,991
- Justice now! Justice now!
- What's happening?!

221
00:13:04,074 --> 00:13:07,328
[driver] Sir, we're stuck!
I think the tire's flat!

222
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:09,079
[activists] Justice now! Justice now!

223
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:10,039
All units, Command.

224
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:12,541
Priority one, crowd control
on Vehicle Two.

225
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:16,837
Secure the detainee and move him
to the lead vehicle, now! Move!

226
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,506
Roger!

227
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:21,800
We're moving the detainee
to the lead vehicle!

228
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:23,302
[activists yelling]

229
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:25,930
Hold onto Datu Rahman!
We need to get him out of here!

230
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,139
- Copy.
- [man] We want justice!

231
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:30,976
[grim music playing]

232
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:43,781
[activists yelling]

233
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:47,368
[activists] Justice! Justice! Justice!

234
00:13:47,451 --> 00:13:49,954
- [Usman] Out of the way! Move!
- Justice now! Justice now!

235
00:13:50,037 --> 00:13:54,917
- Move! Move!
- Justice! Justice! Justice!

236
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:58,504
- [grim music continues]
- [activists yelling]

237
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:12,142
[activists] Justice now! Justice now!

238
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:14,520
Move aside!

239
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:17,147
Justice now! Justice now!

240
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:18,232
- [Lara] Move!
- [indistinct shouting]

241
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:21,777
- [people screaming]
- [gunshots]

242
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:30,327
[man] Stop this now! Cut it out!

243
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:36,584
- [people screaming]
- [dramatic music continues]

244
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:38,794
[Lara] Get out of my way!

245
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,004
[man] Move aside!

246
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:44,800
Where's Datu Rahman? Where's Datu Rahman?!

247
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:46,302
Where the hell is he?!

248
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,472
[man screams] Aah!

249
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:52,391
[people screaming]

250
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:54,226
[Lara] All units, spread out!

251
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:57,229
I need eyes on Datu Rahman
right now! Watch the road exits!

252
00:14:57,813 --> 00:14:59,899
[Lara gasps] We need to find Datu Rahman.

253
00:15:00,524 --> 00:15:02,151
[Lara] I need this wrapped up immediately!

254
00:15:07,948 --> 00:15:08,949
Father, you're safe now.

255
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:11,035
Thank you so much, son. Thank you so much.

256
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:12,661
[inhales sharply] Mm.

257
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,079
[man on radio] <i>Come in! Do you copy?</i>

258
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:16,332
<i>Meet us on the other side of the street.</i>

259
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:17,708
- Copy, copy.
- Let's go!

260
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:21,295
All units, detainee at large!
Continue the search!

261
00:15:21,378 --> 00:15:23,339
Report any sightings immediately!

262
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:25,633
[tense music playing]

263
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:34,224
[grunting, breathing heavily]

264
00:15:34,892 --> 00:15:36,685
[Jalil grunts]

265
00:15:45,277 --> 00:15:48,906
[grunting, breathing heavily]

266
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:51,951
- [tires screech]
- [huffing]

267
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:56,664
[tense music continues]

268
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:07,633
[man] Look! Who are they?

269
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:37,746
[people screaming]

270
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,041
[man] Hey!

271
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,212
- [gunshots]
- [grunting]

272
00:16:45,295 --> 00:16:47,631
- [grunting, shouting]
- [thwacking]

273
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:49,758
[groaning loudly]

274
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:50,801
- [body thuds]
- [table clatters]

275
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:52,553
[grunting and groaning]

276
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:54,138
Let go of me!

277
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:56,432
[grunting and groaning]

278
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:58,475
[gunshot]

279
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:01,103
- [grunting]
- [thwacks]

280
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:03,230
- [Jalil] Ow! Aah!
- [thwacks]

281
00:17:03,313 --> 00:17:04,565
- [grunts]
- [kick lands]

282
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:05,941
[Datu Rahman] Get your hands off me!

283
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:07,526
- Let… Let go of me!
- [man] Hey!

284
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:10,154
I said let go! Get off me!

285
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:13,032
- Stop it! Please!
- [Jalil] Father!

286
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,159
- Jalil!
- [gasping]

287
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:16,785
[grunts] Aah!

288
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:23,459
[tense music playing]

289
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:36,722
Father!

290
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,183
Father!

291
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,394
Father!

292
00:17:43,187 --> 00:17:45,606
[tense music playing]

293
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,697
- [thwacks]
- Aah! Argh!

294
00:17:57,117 --> 00:17:59,369
[man] That's Marcus Reyes. Shoot him down!

295
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:08,087
[suspenseful music playing]

296
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:34,822
[suspenseful music continues]

297
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:40,994
[Rahman] Let me go!
I said, let go! You animals!

298
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:41,912
[man 1 grunts]

299
00:18:41,995 --> 00:18:43,914
- [Rahman] Hands off me!
- [man 2] Shut up!

300
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:47,417
[grunts]

301
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:53,674
[suspenseful music continues]

302
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:55,759
[pained whimper]

303
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:01,598
[Jalil gasping]

304
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,228
All units! Cover all possible exits.

305
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,896
<i>We need to find Datu Rahman!</i>

306
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:10,649
- [Marcus] <i>Lara.</i>
- [Lara] <i>What are you doing here?!</i>

307
00:19:10,732 --> 00:19:12,234
I saw the group who took Datu Rahman.

308
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:13,402
[Marcus] <i>They were armed.</i>

309
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:15,779
You trying to kill yourself?

310
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:18,448
Lara, listen. So many people died!

311
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:21,034
Innocent people, my men… They're all dead!

312
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:22,995
[Marcus] <i>I need to know the truth.</i>

313
00:19:23,078 --> 00:19:25,330
[grunting]

314
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:30,586
[officer] <i>Datu Rahman Abubakar</i>
<i>is a cunning and dangerous man.</i>

315
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:35,132
<i>He has accomplices among</i>
<i>syndicates and civilians.</i>

316
00:19:35,215 --> 00:19:41,388
Criminals like Datu Rahman
must be eliminated.

317
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:46,435
[Jamilah] <i>He is their leader.</i>
<i>He arrested Father.</i>

318
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:56,695
[closing music playing]
